<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to Kansas in Big 12 Title Game</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/24/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kansas-in-big-12-title-game</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/24/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kansas-in-big-12-title-game</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ian Korn throws a pitch against Kansas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/23/DSC03198.jpeg" /><br /><br />SURPRISE, Ariz. – The ninth-ranked and No. 2-seed West Virginia University baseball team fell to 13th-ranked and No. 1-seed Kansas, 9-0, in the Big 12 Tournament final, Saturday afternoon at Surprise Stadium. The Mountaineers fall to 39-14 while the Jayhawks complete the Big 12 double and improve to 42-16.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/DSC03198.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/DSC03198.jpeg"><media:title>Ian Korn throws a pitch against Kansas</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/DSC03198.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 24 May 2026 00:03:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59130</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Advances to Big 12 Tournament Final With Victory Over Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/23/baseball-west-virginia-advances-to-big-12-tournament-final-with-victory-over-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/23/baseball-west-virginia-advances-to-big-12-tournament-final-with-victory-over-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Armani Guzman celebrates with Matthew Graveline after taking the lead against Arizona State" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/23/0Q2A3454.jpg" /><br /><br />SURPRISE, Ariz. – In front of a hostile crowd, the ninth-ranked and No. 2-seed West Virginia University baseball team defeated 21st-ranked and No. 3-seed Arizona State, 7-3, Friday night to advance to the Big 12 Championship game for the third time in program history. The Mountaineers improve to 39-13 while the Sun Devils fall to 37-19.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/0Q2A3454.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/0Q2A3454.jpg"><media:title>Armani Guzman celebrates with Matthew Graveline after taking the lead against Arizona State</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/23/0Q2A3454.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 04:30:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59129</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU’s Baker Says West Tower Press Box Project Moving Along</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/football-wvus-baker-says-west-tower-press-box-project-moving-along</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/football-wvus-baker-says-west-tower-press-box-project-moving-along</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A potential rendering of what the new Milan Puskar Stadium Press Box Tower could look like when it is expected to be completed before the start of the 2028 football season." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/Tower-rendering.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker says he's pleased with the progress being made on the estimated $150 million Milan Puskar Stadium West Tower Press Box project currently in the planning stages.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/Tower-rendering.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/Tower-rendering.jpg"><media:title>A potential rendering of what the new Milan Puskar Stadium Press Box Tower could look like when it is expected to be completed before the start of the 2028 football season.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/Tower-rendering.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 10:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59127</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Defeat Kansas State to Advance in Big 12 Tournament</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-kansas-state-to-advance-in-big-12-tournament</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/22/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-kansas-state-to-advance-in-big-12-tournament</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matthew Graveline celebrates after getting a hit against Kansas State in the Big 12 quarterfinals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" /><br /><br />SURPRISE, Ariz. – The ninth-ranked and No. 2-seed West Virginia University baseball team advanced to the Big 12 Tournament semifinals with a 4-2 win over Kansas State, Thursday night at Surprise Stadium. The Mountaineers improve to 38-13 overall while the Wildcats fall to 30-27.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg"><media:title>Matthew Graveline celebrates after getting a hit against Kansas State in the Big 12 quarterfinals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/DSC02936.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:16:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59128</s:story_id></item><item><title>Eight Mountaineers Selected for NCAA East First Round</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/track-field-eight-mountaineers-selected-for-ncaa-east-first-round</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/track-field-eight-mountaineers-selected-for-ncaa-east-first-round</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Eight Mountaineers selected for the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field East First Round" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Eight members of the West Virginia University track and field team have been selected to compete at the 2026 NCAA East First Round, held May 27-30 in Lexington, Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>Eight Mountaineers selected for the NCAA Outdoor Track and Field East First Round</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/TRACK26_OutdoorRegionalQualifiers_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 15:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59126</s:story_id></item><item><title>Players Era, MGM Resorts International and ESPN Announce Brackets and Tournament Arena Locations for 2026 Players Era Men’s Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/mens-basketball-players-era-mgm-resorts-international-and-espn-announce-brackets-and-tournament-arena-locations-for-2026-players-era-mens-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/mens-basketball-players-era-mgm-resorts-international-and-espn-announce-brackets-and-tournament-arena-locations-for-2026-players-era-mens-championships</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic for the 2026 Players Era 8 tournament" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />NEW YORK/LAS VEGAS – Players Era, an EverWonder Studio company, MGM Resorts International, and ESPN today announced the brackets for the 2026 Players Era Men's Championships, with the Players Era 8 taking place Tuesday-Thursday, November 17-19, at Michelob ULTRA Arena at Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino in Las Vegas, and the Players Era 16 Championship set for Tuesday-Saturday, November 24-28, at T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas and Michelob ULTRA Arena.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic for the 2026 Players Era 8 tournament</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/MBB26_PlayersEraMatchups_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 13:43:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59125</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Varsity Club Accepting Memberships for 2026-27 Year</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/general-wvu-varsity-club-accepting-memberships-for-2026-27-year</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/21/general-wvu-varsity-club-accepting-memberships-for-2026-27-year</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU Varsity Club announces that they are accepting memberships for the 2026-27 year" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The WVU Varsity Club is now accepting memberships and renewals for the 2026-27 year for all former Mountaineer student-athletes and athletics administrators.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>WVU Varsity Club announces that they are accepting memberships for the 2026-27 year</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/21/1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 10:18:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59124</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Set for Big 12 Tournament</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/baseball-west-virginia-set-for-big-12-tournament</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/baseball-west-virginia-set-for-big-12-tournament</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup Big 12 Tournament" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team heads to Surprise, Arizona for the 2026 Big 12 Tournament. The first game for the Mountaineers at Surprise Stadium will be on Thursday, May 21, at 7:30 p.m. at Surprise Stadium against the winner of the No. 7-seed TCU and No. 11-seed Kansas State.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg"><media:title>Matchup Big 12 Tournament</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/BB26_Big12TMatchup_1920x1080_QF.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 19:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59123</s:story_id></item><item><title>Golf Finishes Strong at NCAA Regional</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/golf-finishes-strong-at-ncaa-regional</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/20/golf-finishes-strong-at-ncaa-regional</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU golf team at NCAA Regionals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" /><br /><br />MARANA, Ariz. – West Virginia University golfer Nick Turowski shot -5 in the final round while senior Kaleb Wilson shot -4 today to lead the Mountaineers to their lowest score in an NCAA event at the NCAA Marana Regional at The Gallery Golf Club in Marana, Arizona, on Wednesday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg"><media:title>WVU golf team at NCAA Regionals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/20/GOLF_AZ_REGIONAL_RD3-13.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 18:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59122</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU’s Baker Remains Bullish on Mountaineer Athletics</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/general-wvus-baker-remains-bullish-on-mountaineer-athletics</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/19/general-wvus-baker-remains-bullish-on-mountaineer-athletics</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker visits with media in the Team Room inside the Milan Puskar Center on Tuesday, May 19, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.VA. – Another successful athletic year is nearing its conclusion, which means it's time for West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker to put a bow on things with his yearly spring visit with media.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg"><media:title>WVU Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker visits with media in the Team Room inside the Milan Puskar Center on Tuesday, May 19, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/19/Baker-Main_41J2u.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 19:57:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59121</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>